-- ACS, Spain's Caixa Have Alternatives to CVC for Abertis Deal, Cinco Says
-- Sharon Smyth
-- 2010-07-09T05:35:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/acs-spain-s-caixa-have-alternatives-to-cvc-for-abertis-deal-cinco-says.html

          
          
             Abertis Infraestructuras SA
shareholders Actividades de Construccion y Servicios SA and
Criteria CaixaCorp SA are in talks with two other parties which
are interested in investing in the company, Cinco Dias said.  
 The shareholders, who are currently in talks with CVC
Capital Partners Ltd. to carry out a leveraged buyout of the
company, are in talks with two alternative investors, the
newspaper said, citing unidentified people close to the
operation.   
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        